value.text: Since semiotics studies signs other than linguistic signs as well, it cannot be part of linguistics. But it overlaps iwth it.
"Common examples of semiotics include traffic signs, emojis, and emoticons used in electronic communication, and logos and brands used by international corporations to sell us things"
"signs take the form of words, images, sounds, gestures and objects"
